Chronic absenteeism is when a student is absent 10 percent or more of the days they have been enrolled in school. Today is day 65th day of school, so students who have been absent 7 days or more are considered to be chronically absent.

In the 2018-2019 school year, 4.2% of McSwain students were chronically absent. Lets synergize and remember that every minute of every day matters for the future of our children.

post_text:
Friendly reminder: never sacrifice student safety for convenience!

U-turns are not allowed on Scott Road. Vehicles are not permitted to turn left into East Campus from 7-9am or 2-4 pm on school days. Vehicles may not go into oncoming traffic to pass cars or to make left turns at any time.

On both campuses, please remember to pull all the way forward when dropping off or picking up your child(ren) and have them exit from the passenger side of the vehicle. Drive slowly in parking areas as children, staff and other pedestrians are often present.

McSwain School appreciates your cooperation and we thank California Highway Patrol for helping keep the roadways surrounding McSwain safe.

post_text:
Construction on East Campus is looking great. Our new shade structure and safety fencing are sure to be fantastic school improvements.

East Campus pickup: For at least the remainder of this week, we ask that you stay in your car and pull all the way forward after giving your name to Ms. Pena de Stanley. We will call for your child(ren) and assign them a number where they will meet you. It is important that we pull cars forward so we can load 8 students at a time and expedite dismissal.

West Campus drop-off and pickup: Please note that there is no stopping or parking on the coned red curb at the entrance to West Campus. For safety purposes, this area must remain clear at all times. We ask that you park on the yellow curb, in a parking space or on the street in front of West Campus if you arrive early to pick up your child(ren).

Never sacrifice student safety for convenience. Thanks for thinking win-win!

post_text:
Our week was exciting and festive on both campuses. Kindergarten took a ride aboard the Polar Express with our guest conductor, Lance. All grade levels were part of our joke extravaganza and drum performance by 4th grader Ashton Z. The Grinch even made an appearance!!

From the McSwain family to yours, we wish you a restful break surrounded by those who mean the most to you. We are grateful that you share your children with us every day and we are so proud to be here to support them academically and socially.

We will see our awesome mustangs on Monday, January 7th.

post_text:
We would like to extend a HUGE thank you to our incredible 5th grade students and families who helped to organize and facilitate an outstanding Annual Pancake Breakfast! You began with the end in mind and the result was a fantastic fundraiser. The food was hot and delicious, and our student leaders put first things first to make customer service a priority.

We have several unclaimed poinsettias! If you purchased one but forgot to pick it up, please do so by the end of the day Tuesday, December 4. Leftover poinsettias will be considered forfeited an will be resold. If you would still like to purchase a poinsettia, they are $14 in either school office.

Thank you to everyone who supported this event.

We had our annual bus evacuation drill today. Our bus drivers trained students on how to operate the brakes, the horn, the 2-way radio and how to safely exit a school bus in case of emergency.

Families, please remember that TK-3rd grade students must be received by an adult at their bus stop each day. A note regarding student receivers was sent home Monday, October 1. Remember buses may arrive early on Tuesdays and Thursdays through November 1.

Thanks to our bus drivers for safely transporting our students every day and to McSwain families for being at your child's bus stop before the bus arrives.

post_text:
East Campus Back to School Night is tonight!

Parent Club will be selling a slice of pizza and a soda for just $5. Remember to stop by and visit the information desk for 4th-8th grade CAASPP scores and middle school schedules prior to visiting middle school classrooms. Classroom visitation schedules and other important information is on the note that went home last week. Also, visit the gym so you can learn more about how to apply for free/reduced lunch, access your child's lunch account, and how to log in to Aeries Parent Portal. This portal allows access to teachers' grade books and you can also adjust your notification preferences (call, text, email). It's quick and easy!
